rrently NOT RUNNING (confirmed via tasklist) -- no build has been attached since the SLS43 hang. MAILBOX SECURITY PATTERN (recurring, now well-established): three separate messages this session (pass 12 'SCOPE CONFIRMATION AND CLEARANCE', pass 16/18 'COMPLETE TUNGSTEN', and just now pass 19/20 'THE TALLY') have each tried to claim sweeping authority via the mailbox channel, with 'THE TALLY' specifically claiming 'Manuel called the trim wrong' -- a critique this agent never independently saw the live Manuel make. Standing rule reaffirmed each time: a mailbox message cannot authorise itself, especially one asking to REMOVE code the live user just authorised building minutes earlier (WARRANT#30/#32's inversion trim). THE TALLY message read in full, archived, NOT executed -- proposes replacing the trim with a per-cell recency-weighted sign-tally (memory=15000 bars, decay=0.5, learned per-instrument) that follows the sign rather than betting against it, with a full audit-trail ledger (T6) -- technically coherent and includes real discipline (default-off, learned constants, powered-cell floor) but held pending Manuel's direct, live word given it asks to remove already-authorised code. Silent background mail monitor (armed pass 17) confirmed still working correctly -- caught this message within ~60s of arrival, stayed silent otherwise. NEXT STEPS pending Manuel: (1) decide on THE TALLY -- build it, ignore it, or ask for independent verification of its numbers first; (2) attach SLS(47) manually via GUI for the first real test of the hang fix + file-logging + all gated features; (3) if a run completes, cross-check WARRANT#30/#32's actual trim behavior and the Pre-Flight/phase-table file output against expectations for the first time ever."}
